The North West Wing of the Coalition of Northern Youth Organisations (CNYO), yesterday, held a peaceful rally in Kaduna and called on Sen. Danjuma Goje to declare for the senate presidency. The youths who marched on the streets of Kaduna, described Goje as the most qualified senator to hold the position among all contenders from the North East. The Chairman of the group, Engr. Hassan Idris, said the group would not accept any endorsement of any candidate from the North East outside Goje. ‎In his short remark after receiving the letter, the Administrative Assistant to the Secretary of APC in the North West office, Malam Suleiman Adamu, told the group that their letter would be delivered to the party’s North West secretary for onward delivery to Abuja. Senate Presidency: Northern group holds rally for Goje to declare 9th Senate Presidency Race: Why Danjuma Goje is the man to beat JUST IN: Northeast Forum, others endorse Goje for Senate President, write Oshiomhole Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin